>>63105149
It's a funny mental constraint to see when writing aliens. He's trying to write a species who have clusters of people acting as one "person". In the alien psychology, the group has no actual leader, and makes all decisions democratically. Naturally in the human mind, when observing any group, you will be able to pick out some sort of ring leader. Paza I assume, is that character. She won't be written as a leader, but her actions (so far) seem to be that of a figurehead. She coordinates the flock, and herds them back to the task they need to be doing. If you read closely, the other flocks in different stories have the same dynamic.
I don't want to take the magic out of things, but I find details like this interesting to watch.
